<font color="#FF0000">BEING VIETNAMESE AMERICAN</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jan 23 11:43:55 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Dear Nguyenho,<br><br>
I, too, am a Vietnamese American, whose identity is very much framed by the war.  As the youngest of 7 children &amp; the only one to be born in the US, I have many questions &amp; probably quite a bit of guilt.  My parents came over in the 60s, planning on returning but never doing so.  No one else in the family seems to want to talk about it much, but as the writer in the family, I've been driven to explore the people, the culture, the war, my identity as defined by such, etc. &amp; am now editing an anthology of poetry &amp; fiction by Vietnamese Americans.  I don't know if you do any writing.  If you do, please let me know.  If you don't, please pass the word on to friends.  Deadline is 3/31.  WATERMARK will be released at the end of this year by the Asian American Writers' Workshop (aaww@panix.com).
<p><code>-- btran@hotmail.com  (Barbara Tran) </code><p>


